article.description: Willie Conner hit a career-high eight 3-pointers and finished with 28 points, CJ Massinburg scored 15 and Buffalo cruised to an 87-52 win over Coppin State on Saturday.
article.headline: Conner hits 8 3s, scores 28; Buffalo beats Coppin St 87-52
article.linkText: Conner hits 8 3s, scores 28; Buffalo beats Coppin St 87-52
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. -- Willie Conner hit a career-high eight 3-pointers and finished with 28 points, CJ Massinburg scored 15 and Buffalo cruised to an 87-52 win over Coppin State on Saturday. The Bulls hit 15 3-pointers on 50 percent shooting from deep -- both season highs. Massinburg scored the first seven points and Conner added the final 10, including three 3-pointers, during a 17-4 run that made it 27-15 with seven minutes left in the half and Buffalo (5-5) led the rest of the way. The Bulls took a 41-28 lead into the break, led by double figures throughout the second half and a layup by James Jones gave them a 37-point lead -- their biggest of the game. Dejuan Clayton and Tre' Thomas scored 13 points apiece for Coppin State (0-12). The Eagles, who have lost 13 in a row dating to last season, shot 28 percent (16 of 58).
